sdp/logs/Lead_T-017b_1779518282.log:14104:CHANGELOG.md:246:- Added depth-2 sw_sampler end-to-end test coverage (frac-0116): `tests/test_sw_sampler.py` now includes `SwSamplerEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef source and the SC-side runtime harness `my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd` through one diagnostic lifecycle. The test extracts every documented SynthDef control default (`bufnum`, `amp`, `grain_size_ms=80.0`, `density=12.0`, `position`, `position_rate`, `pitch_transpose_semitones`, `pitch_jitter_semitones`, `attack_sec`, `release_sec`, `gate>=1`, `out_bus=0`, `fx_bus`, `fx_send=0.4`), verifies the integrated granular signal-chain order (`Impulse.kr` -> `TRand.kr` -> `.midiratio` -> `Sweep.ar`/`Phasor.ar` -> `GrainBuf.ar(... bufnum ...)` -> `EnvGen.kr(Env.asr, gate, doneAction: 2)` -> dry `Out.ar(out_bus, ...)` -> parallel `Out.ar(fx_bus, ...)` send) on a comment-stripped source, confirms the dry write to `out_bus` is not scaled by `fx_send` so the parallel-send architecture is preserved, inspects the SC-side runtime harness for source compile, 2-second render, non-silence, FFT spectral peak, gate=0 release tail, and known-content buffer allocation, and round-trips a JSON-safe diagnostic of the SynthDef name, source path, runtime-harness path, defaults, signal-chain stages, stage positions, and runtime checks through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_sw_sampler_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the SCD source and SC-side harness already produced the required one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4669 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-017b_1779518282.log:14110:CHANGELOG.md:526:- Wired active-song human phrase capture into the live listeners: new `senseweave.phrase_capture_runtime.ActiveSongPhraseCapture` gates `PhraseCaptureWriter` on fresh `/tmp/composer_state.json` song context, `midi_keyboard_listener.py` and `theramini_listener.py` now feed qualifying >5s phrases into `samples/keyboard/` and `samples/theramini/` with validated song/key/tempo sidecars, `PhraseCaptureWriter` now exposes `reset()` for safe song-boundary drops, and `human_phrase_capture_verify.py` plus new runtime/integration tests simulate both sources without hardware and validate the resulting paths and tags.
